<seg id=1> Guangxi Made Use of US$150 million in Foreign Capital to Construct River Transportation Infrastructure </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Nanning, March 14th, reporter Lu Hankui.  The Transportation Department of Guangxizhuang Autonomous Region revealed that to date Guangxi has utilized funds from the World Bank, the Asia Bank as well as loans from Holland, Korea, and other countries.  The funds, totaling US$150 million, were used to build infrastructure for river transportation. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> In recent years, the southwest region in China had accelerated construction through the passage to the sea in Guangxi. </seg>
<seg id=4> To resolve the problem of inadequate funding and to open doors to the outside world, Guangxi has made great efforts to attract foreign investment. </seg>
<seg id=5> The second phase of the Xijiang River shipping transportation hub, with a total investment exceeding RMB2 billion, utilized US$80 million from the World Bank. To date, 80% of the major excavation engineering related has been completed, while 50% of the cement work has been completed. </seg>
<seg id=6> The second phase of the engineering in Fangchenggang City (including the highway from Qinzhou City to Fangchenggang City), utilized US$52 million and is projected to be in use by the second half of this year. </seg>
<seg id=7> The engineering of affiliated facilities on Beihai Port utilized funding provided by the Korean government, amounting to US$10 million. </seg>
<seg id=8> The engineering construction of facilities affiliated with Qinzhou Port utilized funding provided by the government of Holland, amounting to US$13 million. </seg>
<seg id=9> To date, all of these projects have been implemented smoothly. </seg>
</p>
